rona fairhead  wikipedia rona fairhead from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search rona fairhead cbe chairwoman of the bbc trust in office  october  –  april  deputy sir roger carr preceded by the lord patten of barnes diane coyle acting succeeded by sir david clementi chair of the bbc board personal details born rona alison haig   august  age  cumbria united kingdom spouses thomas edwin fairhead children  alma mater st catharines college cambridge harvard business school rona alison fairhead cbe née haig born  august  is the former chairman of the bbc trust she is the first woman to hold the post contents  early life and education  career  appearance before public accounts committee  personal life  references early life and educationedit fairhead was born rona haig in cumbria in  and educated at yarm grammar school near stocktonontees north east england before attending st catharines college cambridge she was president of the universitys law society before graduating with a double first in law ba she later obtained a masters in business administration from harvard business school careeredit fairheads early business career was spent at bain  company and morgan stanley in the s before she moved to british aerospace as an independent consultant in  later in  she moved to short brothers shortly after it was bought by bombardier inc she rose to become vicepresident for corporate strategy and public affairs in  and then vicepresident uk aerospace services in  in  she became director of planning and acquisitions for imperial chemical industries before joining the companys executive management team as executive vicepresident for planning and communications in  and continuing as executive vicepresident for strategy and control from  to  from  to  fairhead served as chief financial officer for pearson plc fairhead moved to the financial times group a subsidiary of pearson in  as chief executive she oversaw the sale of several of the groups other titles during her tenure she has also served as a nonexecutive director on the boards of several large corporations including pepsico and is a former director of hsbc holdings and former business ambassador for uk trade  investment she stepped down from her financial times role in  after being overlooked for the position of chair of the pearson group when the post was vacated by the previous incumbent marjorie scardino her leaving package was estimated to be worth over £ million in addition to stock options estimated at over £ million—a contributing factor to a shareholder revolt at pearsons annual general meeting in april  in august  culture secretary sajid javid recommended fairhead as the preferred candidate for the chairmanship of the bbc trust following the departure of chris patten who resigned on health grounds in may sources such as the guardian and the daily telegraph reported that her appointment had caused surprise at the bbc which had expected someone with a higher public profile to get the job others considered for the post were sebastian coe the former chairman of the london organising committee of the olympic and paralympic games and former camelot group chief executive dianne thompson fairhead officially took up the bbc trust role on an acting basis on  september  following approval by the house of commons select committee for culture media and sport she was formally appointed by the privy council of the united kingdom on  october  for a fouryear term beginning the following day in september  fairhead announced that she would not be applying to head the new unitary board replacing the bbc trust appearance before public accounts committeeedit in march  fairhead appeared before the public accounts committee of the house of commons as a nonexecutive director of the swiss subsidiary of hsbc margaret hodge mp the chair of the committee stated that in the light of her performance as an hsbc director she was no longer fit to continue in her role heading the bbc trust mrs hodge was accused of making a bullying attack personal lifeedit fairheads husband tom is a businessman and director of campbell lutyens he was a conservative councillor for earls court in west london from  to  he now serves as an honorary alderman of the royal borough of kensington and chelsea the couple have three children rona fairhead is a qualified pilot and her hobbies include flying and scuba diving towards the end of her tenure with the financial times group fairhead was treated for breast cancer she was appointed a commander of the order of the british empire cbe in the  new years honours list for services to uk industry referencesedit  a b c d e f rona a fairhead debretts people of today   a b c rona fairhead bbc trust chairwoman bbc news bbc  august  retrieved  august    profile rona fairhead bbc news bbc  august  retrieved  september    a b c d e halliday josh  august  rona fairhead chairmanship of bbc trust part of venerable ascent to the top the guardian guardian media group retrieved  september    gilbert nick  february  through the glass ceiling the right chemistry means shes got it all the independent independent print limited retrieved  september    a b c d halliday josh deans jason  august  rona fairhead becomes surprise bbc trust chair choice the guardian guardian media group retrieved  september    mance henry  august  rona fairhead is government’s candidate to chair the bbc trust the financial times retrieved  september    a b c prynne miranda  august  businesswoman rona fairhead the preferred choice for next bbc trust chairman the daily telegraph telegraph media group retrieved  september    orders approved at the privy council on th october  pdf privy council office  october    bbc trust chair rona fairhead to leave role bbc news online  september  retrieved  september    syal sweney  march  margaret hodge accused of abusive and bullying attack on bbc trust chair the guardian guardian media group   no  the london gazette supplement  december  pp –  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleronafairheadoldid categories  birthsliving peoplealumni of st catharines college cambridgechairmen of the bbccommanders of the order of the british empireharvard business school alumnitrustees of the british broadcasting corporationpeople from cumbriawomen chief financial officershidden categories pages containing london gazette template with parameter supp set to y navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view rona fairhead  wikipedia rona fairhead from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search rona fairhead cbe chairwoman of the bbc trust in office  october  –  april  deputy sir roger carr preceded by the lord patten of barnes diane coyle acting succeeded by sir david clementi chair of the bbc board personal details born rona alison haig   august  age  cumbria united kingdom spouses thomas edwin fairhead children  alma mater st catharines college cambridge harvard business school rona alison fairhead cbe née haig born  august  is the former chairman of the bbc trust she is the first woman to hold the post contents  early life and education  career  appearance before public accounts committee  personal life  references early life and educationedit fairhead was born rona haig in cumbria in  and educated at yarm grammar school near stocktonontees north east england before attending st catharines college cambridge she was president of the universitys law society before graduating with a double first in law ba she later obtained a masters in business administration from harvard business school careeredit fairheads early business career was spent at bain  company and morgan stanley in the s before she moved to british aerospace as an independent consultant in  later in  she moved to short brothers shortly after it was bought by bombardier inc she rose to become vicepresident for corporate strategy and public affairs in  and then vicepresident uk aerospace services in  in  she became director of planning and acquisitions for imperial chemical industries before joining the companys executive management team as executive vicepresident for planning and communications in  and continuing as executive vicepresident for strategy and control from  to  from  to  fairhead served as chief financial officer for pearson plc fairhead moved to the financial times group a subsidiary of pearson in  as chief executive she oversaw the sale of several of the groups other titles during her tenure she has also served as a nonexecutive director on the boards of several large corporations including pepsico and is a former director of hsbc holdings and former business ambassador for uk trade  investment she stepped down from her financial times role in  after being overlooked for the position of chair of the pearson group when the post was vacated by the previous incumbent marjorie scardino her leaving package was estimated to be worth over £ million in addition to stock options estimated at over £ million—a contributing factor to a shareholder revolt at pearsons annual general meeting in april  in august  culture secretary sajid javid recommended fairhead as the preferred candidate for the chairmanship of the bbc trust following the departure of chris patten who resigned on health grounds in may sources such as the guardian and the daily telegraph reported that her appointment had caused surprise at the bbc which had expected someone with a higher public profile to get the job others considered for the post were sebastian coe the former chairman of the london organising committee of the olympic and paralympic games and former camelot group chief executive dianne thompson fairhead officially took up the bbc trust role on an acting basis on  september  following approval by the house of commons select committee for culture media and sport she was formally appointed by the privy council of the united kingdom on  october  for a fouryear term beginning the following day in september  fairhead announced that she would not be applying to head the new unitary board replacing the bbc trust appearance before public accounts committeeedit in march  fairhead appeared before the public accounts committee of the house of commons as a nonexecutive director of the swiss subsidiary of hsbc margaret hodge mp the chair of the committee stated that in the light of her performance as an hsbc director she was no longer fit to continue in her role heading the bbc trust mrs hodge was accused of making a bullying attack personal lifeedit fairheads husband tom is a businessman and director of campbell lutyens he was a conservative councillor for earls court in west london from  to  he now serves as an honorary alderman of the royal borough of kensington and chelsea the couple have three children rona fairhead is a qualified pilot and her hobbies include flying and scuba diving towards the end of her tenure with the financial times group fairhead was treated for breast cancer she was appointed a commander of the order of the british empire cbe in the  new years honours list for services to uk industry referencesedit  a b c d e f rona a fairhead debretts people of today   a b c rona fairhead bbc trust chairwoman bbc news bbc  august  retrieved  august    profile rona fairhead bbc news bbc  august  retrieved  september    a b c d e halliday josh  august  rona fairhead chairmanship of bbc trust part of venerable ascent to the top the guardian guardian media group retrieved  september    gilbert nick  february  through the glass ceiling the right chemistry means shes got it all the independent independent print limited retrieved  september    a b c d halliday josh deans jason  august  rona fairhead becomes surprise bbc trust chair choice the guardian guardian media group retrieved  september    mance henry  august  rona fairhead is government’s candidate to chair the bbc trust the financial times retrieved  september    a b c prynne miranda  august  businesswoman rona fairhead the preferred choice for next bbc trust chairman the daily telegraph telegraph media group retrieved  september    orders approved at the privy council on th october  pdf privy council office  october    bbc trust chair rona fairhead to leave role bbc news online  september  retrieved  september    syal sweney  march  margaret hodge accused of abusive and bullying attack on bbc trust chair the guardian guardian media group   no  the london gazette supplement  december  pp –  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleronafairheadoldid categories  birthsliving peoplealumni of st catharines college cambridgechairmen of the bbccommanders of the order of the british empireharvard business school alumnitrustees of the british broadcasting corporationpeople from cumbriawomen chief financial officershidden categories pages containing london gazette template with parameter supp set to y navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurren